alerts.description: ...STRONG WINDS POSSIBLE IN THE MOUNTAINS AND FOOTHILLS WEDNESDAY... .Strong westerly flow aloft is expected over Wyoming and northern Colorado from later tonight through Wednesday. This will bring gusty winds to the mountain ridges and eastern slopes of the front range. Gusty winds will also spread over the foothills of Larimer, Boulder and Jefferson Counties. The gusty winds are expected to continue through the day and into Wednesday evening before diminishing. ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO MIDNIGHT MDT WEDNESDAY NIGHT... The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a High Wind Warning, which is in effect from 9 PM this evening to midnight MDT Wednesday night. The High Wind Watch is no longer in effect. * TIMING...Winds will begin increasing late this evening. Gusty winds will continue through the day Wednesday and begin diminishing Wednesday evening. * WINDS...West winds 30 to 50 mph with gusts in excess 75 mph. * IMPACTS...Travel may become difficult over high mountain passes and along the Peak To Peak Highway due to crosswinds. Power outages will be possible from trees blowing onto power lines. Secure lightweight outdoor items to prevent them from blowing away.
